Because concentration represents the amount of a selected substance in the total amount of all components, its analysis requires application of appropriate mathematical methods (Aitchison 2003; Pawlowsky-Glahn and Buccianti 2011). The sample space of our measurement results is a set of compositions. Composition of a system composed of D components can be calculated by the closure operation C, defined as follows:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
